# AWIT RIDDLES
AWIT_RIDDLE_1='I follow you in the light, but disappear in the dark. I grow tall when the candle is low. What am i ?'
AWIT_ANSWER_1=shadow
AWIT_HINT_1='Hint: Cast by your body.'

AWIT_RIDDLE_2='The person whome makes it has no need of it; the person who buys it has no use of it. The person who uses it can neither see nor feel it. What am i ?'
AWIT_ANSWER_2=coffin
AWIT_HINT_2='Hint: Final resting place.'

AWIT_RIDDLE_3='I am not alive, but I can die. What am I?'
AWIT_ANSWER_3=battery
AWIT_HINT_3='Hint: Powers your torch.'

AWIT_RIDDLE_4='What has roots as nobody sees, is taller than trees, up, up it goes, and yet never grows?'
AWIT_ANSWER_4=mountain
AWIT_HINT_4='Hint: Stands tall in the distance.'

AWIT_RIDDLE_5='I can be written, I can be spoken, I can be exposed, I can be broken. What am I?'
AWIT_ANSWER_5=secret
AWIT_HINT_5='Hint: Keep it hidden'

AWIT_RIDDLE_6='What has many keys but can'
AWIT_ANSWER_6=piano
AWIT_HINT_6='Hint: Makes music.'

AWIT_RIDDLE_7='I am always hungry, I must always be fed. The finger I touch will soon turn red. What am I?'
AWIT_ANSWER_7=fire
AWIT_HINT_7='Hint: Lights the darkness'

AWIT_RIDDLE_8='What can run but never walks, has a mouth but never talks, has a head but never weeps, has a bed but never sleeps?'
AWIT_ANSWER_8=river
AWIT_HINT_8='Hint: Flows through the dungeon.'

AWIT_RIDDLE_9='I have a thousand wheels, but move I do not. Call me what I am, call me a lot. What am I?'
AWIT_ANSWER_9='parking lot'
AWIT_HINT_9='Hint: Where carriages rest.'

AWIT_RIDDLE_10='What belongs to you, but other people use it more than you?'
AWIT_ANSWER_10='your name'
AWIT_HINT_10='Hint: Others call you by it.'

# DEANVER RIDDLES
DEANVER_RIDDLE_1='The more you take from me, the bigger I get. What am I?'
DEANVER_ANSWER_1=hole
DEANVER_HINT_1='Hint: Digging in the dungeon floor creates me.'

DEANVER_RIDDLE_2='I have cities but no houses. I have mountains but no trees. I have water but no fish. What am I?'
DEANVER_ANSWER_2=map
DEANVER_HINT_2='Hint: Look at the wall.'

DEANVER_RIDDLE_3='What can you catch but not throw?'
DEANVER_ANSWER_3=cold
DEANVER_HINT_3='Hint: You might get this in a damp dungeon.'

DEANVER_RIDDLE_4='I speak without a mouth and hear without ears. What am I?'
DEANVER_ANSWER_4=echo
DEANVER_HINT_4='Hint: Shout and I'

DEANVER_RIDDLE_5='What has hands but cannot clap?'
DEANVER_ANSWER_5=clock
DEANVER_HINT_5='Hint: Tells time on the wall.'

DEANVER_RIDDLE_6='I have a neck but no head. What am I?'
DEANVER_ANSWER_6=bottle
DEANVER_HINT_6='Hint: Holds potions.'

DEANVER_RIDDLE_7='What gets wet while drying?'
DEANVER_ANSWER_7=towel
DEANVER_HINT_7='Hint: After a bath.'

DEANVER_RIDDLE_8='I have a face but no eyes. What am I?'
DEANVER_ANSWER_8=clock
DEANVER_HINT_8='Hint: Has numbers.'

DEANVER_RIDDLE_9='What can travel around the world while staying in a corner?'
DEANVER_ANSWER_9=stamp
DEANVER_HINT_9='Hint: On a letter.'

DEANVER_RIDDLE_10='I have a tail but no body. What am I?'
DEANVER_ANSWER_10=coin
DEANVER_HINT_10='Hint: Flip me for luck.'

# HAYES RIDDLES
HAYES_RIDDLE_1='I bind the prisoner tight, link by link. Break one, and I am still strong. What am I?'
HAYES_ANSWER_1=chain
HAYES_HINT_1='Hint: Made of iron rings.'

HAYES_RIDDLE_2='I have a tongue but cannot talk. I have a sole but cannot walk. What am I?'
HAYES_ANSWER_2=shoe
HAYES_HINT_2='Hint: On your feet.'

HAYES_RIDDLE_3='What has a head and a tail but no body?'
HAYES_ANSWER_3=coin
HAYES_HINT_3='Hint: Flip for luck.'

HAYES_RIDDLE_4='I can be long or short, I can be grown or bought. What am I?'
HAYES_ANSWER_4=hair
HAYES_HINT_4='Hint: On your head.'

HAYES_RIDDLE_5='What has a neck but no head?'
HAYES_ANSWER_5=bottle
HAYES_HINT_5='Hint: Holds potions.'

HAYES_RIDDLE_6='I have keys but open no locks. What am I?'
HAYES_ANSWER_6=piano
HAYES_HINT_6='Hint: Makes music.'

HAYES_RIDDLE_7='What can you hold in your right hand but never in your left?'
HAYES_ANSWER_7='your left hand'
HAYES_HINT_7='Hint: Try it.'

HAYES_RIDDLE_8='I have a bed but never sleep. What am I?'
HAYES_ANSWER_8=river
HAYES_HINT_8='Hint: Flows through the dungeon.'

HAYES_RIDDLE_9='What has an eye but cannot see?'
HAYES_ANSWER_9=needle
HAYES_HINT_9='Hint: Used for sewing.'

HAYES_RIDDLE_10='I am taken from a mine and shut in a wooden case. What am I?'
HAYES_ANSWER_10=pencil
HAYES_HINT_10='Hint: Used for writing.'

# JOJAN RIDDLES
JOJAN_RIDDLE_1='I have no voice, but I can tell you everything. I have no ears, but I hear you. What am I?'
JOJAN_ANSWER_1=echo
JOJAN_HINT_1='Hint: Shout in a hallway.'

JOJAN_RIDDLE_2='The more of me you take, the more you leave behind. What am I?'
JOJAN_ANSWER_2=footsteps
JOJAN_HINT_2='Hint: Walking leaves me.'

JOJAN_RIDDLE_3='I can be cracked, made, told, and played. What am I?'
JOJAN_ANSWER_3=joke
JOJAN_HINT_3='Hint: Makes you laugh.'

JOJAN_RIDDLE_4='What has a heart that doesn'
JOJAN_ANSWER_4='deck of cards'
JOJAN_HINT_4='Hint: Used for games.'

JOJAN_RIDDLE_5='I am not alive, but I grow. I don'
JOJAN_ANSWER_5=fire
JOJAN_HINT_5='Hint: Lights the darkness.'

JOJAN_RIDDLE_6='What can you break, even if you never pick it up or touch it?'
JOJAN_ANSWER_6=promise
JOJAN_HINT_6='Hint: Words can break it.'

JOJAN_RIDDLE_7='I have cities, but no houses. I have forests, but no trees. What am I?'
JOJAN_ANSWER_7=map
JOJAN_HINT_7='Hint: Shows the way.'

JOJAN_RIDDLE_8='What has a ring but no finger?'
JOJAN_ANSWER_8=phone
JOJAN_HINT_8='Hint: It rings.'

JOJAN_RIDDLE_9='I am full of holes but still holds water. What am I?'
JOJAN_ANSWER_9=sponge
JOJAN_HINT_9='Hint: Used for cleaning.'

JOJAN_RIDDLE_10='What goes up but never comes down?'
JOJAN_ANSWER_10=age
JOJAN_HINT_10='Hint: Time passes.'

# KIRBY RIDDLES
KIRBY_RIDDLE_1='I have a head but no face, and a bed but never sleep. I have teeth but cannot bite. What am I?'
KIRBY_ANSWER_1=key
KIRBY_HINT_1='Hint: You use me to open the door behind me.'

KIRBY_RIDDLE_2='What has a lock but no door?'
KIRBY_ANSWER_2='lock of hair'
KIRBY_HINT_2='Hint: Found on your head.'

KIRBY_RIDDLE_3='I open paths but have no feet. What am I?'
KIRBY_ANSWER_3=key
KIRBY_HINT_3='Hint: Fits in a lock.'

KIRBY_RIDDLE_4='What has many teeth but cannot bite?'
KIRBY_ANSWER_4=comb
KIRBY_HINT_4='Hint: Used for hair.'

KIRBY_RIDDLE_5='I guard treasures but have no sword. What am I?'
KIRBY_ANSWER_5=lock
KIRBY_HINT_5='Hint: Needs a key.'

KIRBY_RIDDLE_6='What has a ring but no finger?'
KIRBY_ANSWER_6=key
KIRBY_HINT_6='Hint: Opens doors.'

KIRBY_RIDDLE_7='I have a spine but no bones. What am I?'
KIRBY_ANSWER_7=book
KIRBY_HINT_7='Hint: Holds knowledge.'

KIRBY_RIDDLE_8='What has pages but no face?'
KIRBY_ANSWER_8=book
KIRBY_HINT_8='Hint: You read me.'

KIRBY_RIDDLE_9='I light the way but have no eyes. What am I?'
KIRBY_ANSWER_9=torch
KIRBY_HINT_9='Hint: Found in dungeons.'

KIRBY_RIDDLE_10='What has a handle but no door?'
KIRBY_ANSWER_10=sword
KIRBY_HINT_10='Hint: A warrior'

# PATRICK RIDDLES
PATRICK_RIDDLE_1='I am the end of the dungeon, but the start of freedom. I am heavy wood and iron bars. What am I?'
PATRICK_ANSWER_1=gate
PATRICK_HINT_1='Hint: It stands between you and the outside world.'

PATRICK_RIDDLE_2='I have a spine but no bones, pages but no face. I hold secrets of the dungeon. What am I?'
PATRICK_ANSWER_2=spellbook
PATRICK_HINT_2='Hint: Wizards use me.'

PATRICK_RIDDLE_3='What has a crown but no head, a trunk but no body?'
PATRICK_ANSWER_3=tree
PATRICK_HINT_3='Hint: Found in the forest.'

PATRICK_RIDDLE_4='I can be cracked, I can be made, I can be told, I can be played. What am I?'
PATRICK_ANSWER_4=joke
PATRICK_HINT_4='Hint: Makes you laugh.'

PATRICK_RIDDLE_5='The more you take, the more you leave behind. What am I?'
PATRICK_ANSWER_5=footsteps
PATRICK_HINT_5='Hint: Walking leaves me.'

PATRICK_RIDDLE_6='I have a mouth but cannot speak, I have a bed but cannot sleep. What am I?'
PATRICK_ANSWER_6=river
PATRICK_HINT_6='Hint: Flows through the dungeon.'

PATRICK_RIDDLE_7='What has an eye but cannot see, a tongue but cannot taste?'
PATRICK_ANSWER_7=needle
PATRICK_HINT_7='Hint: Used for sewing.'

PATRICK_RIDDLE_8='I am always in front of you but cannot be seen. What am I?'
PATRICK_ANSWER_8=future
PATRICK_HINT_8='Hint: What'

PATRICK_RIDDLE_9='What can you catch but not throw, that grows in the dungeon'
PATRICK_ANSWER_9=cold
PATRICK_HINT_9='Hint: You might get this.'

PATRICK_RIDDLE_10='I have cities but no houses, forests but no trees, rivers but no water. What am I?'
PATRICK_ANSWER_10=map
PATRICK_HINT_10='Hint: Look at the wall.'

